    • Method Detail

      • getName

        default @NonNull java.lang.String getName()
        Returns the name of a MinXML element. It is not guaranteed that this is interned but it is guaranteed to be non-null.
        Returns:
        the element name

      • getInternedName

        @NonNull java.lang.String getInternedName()
        Returns the interned name of a MinXML element. Guaranteed to be a non-null interned string.
        Returns:
        interned version of the element name

      • hasName

        default boolean hasName(@Nullable java.lang.String name)
        Returns true if the name of the element is equal to the given string. Equivalent to this.getName().equals( name ). Note that although the name may never be null, we allow testing against null for convenience even though that test will always be false.
        Parameters:
        name - the name we are checking
        Returns:
        true if the element has that name

      • setName

        default void setName(@NonNull java.lang.String x)
              throws java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
        Changes the name of the element to the given string. Note that an implementation of MinXML is not obliged to support this method and may throw an exception. The name may not be null, otherwise a {link RuntimeException} is thrown.
        Parameters:
        name - the name we are setting
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if the implementing class cannot support this method
